frameDefinitions: An Agent goes to an Event and is present in a relatively non-participatory way.
A Total has a Part, either  as a member of an aggregate or as  a constituent part of a simple entity.
An Inspector directs his/her perceptual attention to a Ground to ascertain whether the Ground is intact or  whether an Unwanted_entity is present.
In a text, a Source_of_information is given that provides a reader of the text with further Information relevant to the text.

A new Employee obtains a Position with an Employer, with which there are certain Tasks associated; in exchange for the performance of these Tasks, the Employee receives Compensation from the Employer.
An Agent matches location with an Entity in order to fulfill some  Purpose.
frameExamples: The Angolan guerrillas will <t>attend</t> a September meeting in Zaire.
The police removed Flonnory and Barbour from the automobile and <t>frisked</t> them for weapons.
In Densmore's days it was sometimes made of an old-fashioned man's celluloid collar (<t>cf.</t> Densmore 1943: 116).

listRoleDefinitions: The  <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who chooses to make himself present at the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Event</fen> is the deliberate set of happenings given at a particular time and place.
When the <fen>Agent</fen> attends the <fen>Event</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> attends the <fen>Event</fen>.
A complex entity, either an aggregate or a unit, of which a <fen>Part</fen>,  a constituent or a component, is specified.
A component or constituent that is specified to form part of the <fen>Total</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Total</fen> includes the <fen>Part</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Total</fen> includes the <fen>Part</fen>.
The person who inspects the <fen>Ground</fen> to see if it is intact or without blemish.
The entity that the <fen>Inspector</fen> inspects with his senses to ascertain whether it is intact.
An entity whose presence would impair the acceptability or usefulness of the <fen>Ground</fen>.

Some of the words in this frame occur with a constituent that expresses the desired outcome of the inspection.  Normally this constituent is a PP Complement headed by <ment>for</ment>, or a <ment>to</ment>-marked VP Complement.
The desirable state of affairs which the <fen>Inspector</fen> hopes to find to obtain when inspecting the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Inspector</fen> examines the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Source_of_information</fen> is referred to as a source of information related to the current text.
The person who enters an employment relation with an <fen>Employer</fen>.
The person (or institution) that the <fen>Employee</fen> enters an employment relationship with.
The label given to a particular type of employment.
The action that the <fen>Employee</fen> is obligated to do for the <fen>Employer</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when an <fen>Employee</fen> signs on with an <fen>Employer</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Employee</fen> enteres an employment relationship with an <fen>Employer</fen>.
The sentient entity that is temporarily with the <fen>Entity</fen> in order to fulfil some <fen>Purpose</fen>.

The physical entity that is permanently associated with entities or characteristics that the <fen>Agent</fen> wishes to use for some <fen>Purpose</fen>.  During the visit, the <fen>Agent</fen> matches location with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which a visit is made.
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen> during the visit.
